{
  "stem": "1042.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was 17 years old when I decide to take up auto mechanics and driving lessons.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My sister was very unhappy about my choice to become an auto mechanic, as she felt that this was not a prestigious profession.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I, on the other hand, was very enthusiastic about anything on wheels.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When I was 18 years old, as an orphan, I was allowed to receive my diving license, which was three years earlier than normal.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "At that time, I was a bicycle- and motorcycle-racing driver.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The permission that [NON-ENGLISH] sport club gave to me to drive at this age eventually saved my life.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Once I was in a situation where the commandant get took out his revolver and was about to kill me, when someone stopped him by telling him that I was the only mechanic they had in the camp.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "From that day on, I used to go repair his cars.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Later, I worked in [INAUDIBLE] where I first met Mr.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Oskar Schindler.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He told me that Plaszow concentration camp would be liquidated and then he would take me and the five other mechanics to his new factory in Brunnlitz, where I would be responsible for the maintenance and upkeep of his machines.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He was my lifesaver.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The only thing I worried about was that this was a dream and could not be a reality-- to receive 2,000 calories a day, and to be treated like a human being, and not to have to worry about being shot anytime.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I remember Mrs.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Schindler very well, how she used to leave and many of them she brought to our half-frozen, hungry people.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And she was the one-- she used to prepare the food for them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Nobody in our camp was killed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Only one girl died, from natural causes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Mr.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Schindler arranged for the funeral services for her, with Rabbi Levertov.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We had a rabbi also with us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "He also gave us a safe corner in the camp where, together with the rabbi, we would hold Shabbat services.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Whenever he found out that there were dead horses in the battlefield, he took great risk by going out there and pick them up, load them on the wagons, bring them back to camp, and ordered to cook them, to feed us with.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Also, whenever he walked through the factory, he would like to light up a cigarette and drop it and then light up another one and another one, again, dropping it so that we would pick them up and smoke them.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "He offered us priceless protections.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "At Schindler's camp, no Nazi guard was allowed to shoot at us simply because we were Jews or because they just felt like doing so.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "He spent a fortune bribing the powerful SS men.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I remember when he took a few of us into a confidence and told us that one day we would be called by the SS to assemble in Opernplatz where they will count to kill us because the Russians were approaching, and it looked like the war was coming to end.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And, that moment, should run to the basement where had prepared rifles, guns, and ammunitions for us protection.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Start shooting, he said.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Some of you might get killed, but some of you might survive.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Otherwise, all of you be killed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Thanks God did not come to such a situation, as the Germans did not have time to do this.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "There are no words to express the endless favors that the Schindlers extended us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "It is not only Steven Spielberg, Poldek Page, and Thomas Keneally brought the truth of the Holocaust of the [INAUDIBLE] but the few-- those that denied that the Holocaust ever exist.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "This Holocaust happened in our lifetime.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And, to those of us who lived through it, we find it hard to believe that in today's time there are still people who deny the very existence of it.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Our children, grandchildren, great-grandchildren will learn about the tragedy of the Second World War.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "We can only hope and pray that it will never happen again.'",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This is my dearest wife, Natalie.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I was in Israel, I wasn't married.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But my very close friends, they send me papers I should come from Israel because they want to be together with me.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was 1953.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And coming to Canada, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was looking for something to do.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then I was looking for some girls, for some friends.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And finally, I was not married, so I find my dear wife.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She was, at that time-- she was a widow with two children.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We knew each other from before the war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She used to live in my neighborhood, as a young girl.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we were going around, five years, because it was two children.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
